  "type": "mcq",
  "stem": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">The height, in feet, of an object <span class=\"italic\">x</span> seconds after it is thrown straight up in the air can be modeled by the function <span class=\"math_expression \"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"h of x equals, negative 16 x squared, plus 20 x, plus 5\"></span></span>. Based on the model, which of the following statements best interprets the equation <span class=\"math_expression \"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"h of 1 point 4 equals, 1 point 6 4\"></span></span> ?</p>\n",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
      "id": "a",
      "content": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">The height of the object 1.4 seconds after being thrown straight up in the air is 1.64 feet.</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "id": "b",
      "content": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">The height of the object 1.64 seconds after being thrown straight up in the air is 1.4 feet.</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "id": "c",
      "content": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">The height of the object 1.64 seconds after being thrown straight up in the air is approximately 1.4 times as great as its initial height.</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "id": "d",
      "content": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">The speed of the object 1.4 seconds after being thrown straight up in the air is approximately 1.64 feet per second.</p>\n"
    }
